Serves 4 - 6.Ingredients:750g lamb steaks, sliced30ml (2 tbsp) oilSeeds scraped from 1 black cardamom pod5ml (1 tsp) garlic paste5ml (1 tsp) ginger paste10ml (2 tsp) chilli flakes1 large onion, slicedA few sprigs fresh thyme4 jalape o peppers, halvedAsha's spice box: A glossary of exotic Indian seasonings1 firm red tomato, cut into wedgesSalt, to tasteMethod:1) Trim any visible fat off the slices of lamb. Heat the oil in a pan and fry the meat in a single layer until lightly browned on both sides. Sprinkle with cardamom seeds. Add garlic, ginger and chilli flakes.2) Reduce heat and cook gently until the meat juices are released. Add onion and thyme. Place the jalape os and tomato wedges over the meat. Season. Cover saucepan with a lid and simmer for 8-10 minutes. The meat should cook gently without having to add stock or water.